-- South Africa Defeats India by Innings and 25 Runs in First Cricket Test
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2010-12-20T08:37:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/south-africa-defeats-india-by-innings-and-25-runs-in-first-cricket-test.html
South Africa beat top-ranked India
by an innings and 25 runs in their series opening cricket Test
at Centurion.  Morne Morkel  and  Dale Steyn  took the remaining two Indian
wickets on the final morning to dismiss the touring team for 459
in its second innings. The South Africans had amassed 620-4
declared after skittling India for 136 in its first innings.  Sachin Tendulkar  finished on 111 not out after yesterday
becoming the first player in 133 years of elite Test cricket to
register 50 centuries.   The second Test starts Dec. 26 in Durban before the best-
of-three contest concludes in Cape Town from Jan. 2. South
Africa has won all four previous home series against India.  To contact the reporter on this story:
